    <body>
      <div>
        <head rend="center">
        <title type="main">Understand whitey</title>
      </head>
    </div>
    <div rend="center"></div>
    <byline><persName ref="#MM"><hi rend="italics">Mike McNair</hi></persName>
  </byline>
</body>
</text>
<text>
  <body>
<p>
<time>In prior years</time>, <persName ref="#CRL">civil rights leaders</persName>
have <interp ana="#ACT">pointed an accusing</interp> <choice><orig>Anger</orig><reg>finger</reg></choice> at <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">white
America</interp></affiliation>, <interp ana="#ACT">screaming racism</interp> <choice><orig>of</orig><reg>at</reg></choice> the top
of <interp ana="#AFAM">their</interp> lungs.</p>
<p>The <interp ana="#ACT">reply</interp> was<choice><orig>;</orig><reg>:</reg></choice> <said><affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">“We aren't racist</interp></affiliation><choice><orig>l</orig><reg>!</reg></choice>
It’s <choice><orig>J</orig><reg>j</reg></choice>ust that <interp ana="#AFAM">those people</interp> are so <affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">un-­
civilized, so uncultured, so stupid, so
filthy</interp></affiliation>. <interp ana="#CAUC">Let’s</interp> <interp ana="#ACT">face it</interp>—<interp ana="#CAUC">we’re just better
than</interp> <interp ana="#AFAM">they</interp> are. Maybe <time>in a <num>few</num> years</time>,
<time>when <interp ana="#AFAM">they’re</interp> <interp ana="#ACT">raised up</interp> to <interp ana="#CAUC">our</interp> <affiliation>stan­<add>-</add>
dards</affiliation></time>, <interp ana="#CAUC">we’ll</interp> <interp ana="#ACT">allow</interp> <interp ana="#AFAM">them</interp> <interp ana="#CAUC">to exist</interp> with
<interp ana="#CAUC">us</interp>.”</said></p>
<p><time>Now in this great age</time>, <persName ref="#CRL">the civil rights
leaders</persName> are <time>still</time> <interp ana="#ACT">pointing an accusing
finger</interp> at <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">white America</interp></affiliation><choice><orig>,</orig><reg>.</reg></choice></p>
<p>Yet the <interp ana="#ACT">reply</interp> is <time>now</time> a little different:
<said>“Okay, <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">we are racist</interp></affiliation>. But look at
<num>some</num> of <affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">your organizations</interp></affiliation>. Aren’t <interp ana="#AFAM">they</interp>
<affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">all one race</interp></affiliation>? Isn’t this <affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">new separatist
movement</interp></affiliation> really a <interp ana="#AFAM">form of racism</interp>?”</said></p>
<p>Thus it would appear as though <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">the
country</interp></affiliation> is <time>now</time> <interp ana="#ACT">preoccupied with name-­
calling</interp>. <said><interp ana="#OTHER">“Commies, fascists, nazis</interp>,and
<time>now</time> <affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">racists</interp></affiliation>.<add>"</add></said> The atmosphere of <said>“Don’t
call me <interp ana="#ASLUR">nigger</interp>, <choice><orig>whltey</orig><reg><interp ana="#CAUC">whitey</interp></reg></choice>—Don’t call me
<interp ana="#CSLUR">whitey</interp>, <interp ana="#AFAM">nigger</interp>,”</said> prevails over every
<interp ana="#ACT">interracial confrontation</interp>.</p>
<p><time>Once again</time>, each side proved that
the lack of <interp ana="#ACT">good effective communica­-
tion</interp> had caused wholesale ignorance and
<choice><orig>m isunder standing</orig><reg>misunderstanding</reg></choice>.</p>
<p>Few <interp ana="#CAUC">whites</interp> recognized that <interp ana="#AFAM">the black
men</interp> who refer to <interp ana="#CSLUR">Whitey</interp> are not neces­<add>-</add>
sarily referring to <interp ana="#CAUC">the white race</interp>. <interp ana="#CAUC">Whites</interp>
<interp ana="#ACT">don’t understand</interp> that <term><interp ana="#CAUC">white</interp></term>, like <term><interp ana="AFAM">black</interp></term>, is
a <affiliation><term>term for a state of mind</term></affiliation>.</p>
<p>A good definition of <term>white</term> as <affiliation>a state
of mind</affiliation> would be—one whose standards
coincide with the <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">higher social classes</interp></affiliation>
as a result of being <choice><orig>I</orig><reg>i</reg></choice>n a <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">higher social
bracket</interp></affiliation>.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<p><affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">Strong family structures, strong ed­-
ucational background, numerous vo­-
cational opportunities and multitudes of
legal advantages</interp></affiliation>.</p>
<p>In short, a <term><affiliation>synonym</affiliation></term> for <term>white</term> is <term>rich</term>­<add>--</add>
defining <term>rich</term> to mean <affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">not poor</interp></affiliation>.</p>
<p>A <term><affiliation>synonym</affiliation></term> for <term>black</term> is <term><affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">poor</interp></affiliation></term>.</p>
<p>In the <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">white culture</interp></affiliation>, <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">entertainment
and amusement</interp></affiliation> varied with the taste of
<affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">the Individual</interp></affiliation>. <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">Restaurants, night clubs,
movies, trips abroad, plays, little
leagues, playgrounds, formal evening
parties, camp-outs and other luxuries</interp></affiliation>
were <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">common place</interp></affiliation>.</p>
<p>The <affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">black culture</interp></affiliation>, on the contrary,
<interp ana="#ACT">boasted</interp> of the <affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">endurance</interp></affiliation> of <interp ana="#AFAM">the poor</interp>.</p>
<p><interp ana="#AFAM">Children</interp> <interp ana="#ACT">seldom saw a blade of grass</interp>.
<interp ana="#ACT">Improvisation</interp> became one of <affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">their
greatest attributes</interp></affiliation>. <interp ana="#AFAM">They</interp> even had to
<interp ana="#ACT">improvise on food</interp>. But <time>too often</time>, there
was <affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">nothing to improvise with</interp></affiliation>.</p>
<p>Since <interp ana="#AFAM">black</interp> had been an <affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">unstudied,
disrespected culture</interp></affiliation> in <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">white America</interp></affiliation>,
<num>few</num> <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">rich Caucasians</interp></affiliation> saw t<choice><orig>n</orig><reg>h</reg></choice>e need to
<interp ana="#ACT">think black</interp>. <time>Now that the need has
arisen</time>, <affiliation><interp ana="#CAUC">rich Caucasians</interp></affiliation> <interp ana="#ACT">find it dif­-
ficult to think poor</interp>.</p>
<p>Obviously, <num>many</num> <interp ana="#AFAM">poor</interp> lacked the ability
<interp ana="#ACT">to think rich or white</interp>. <affiliation><persName ref="#MM">These state­-
ments</persName></affiliation> should have caused <num>enough</num> con­<add>-</add>
fusion to <interp ana="#ACT">warrant several questions</interp>.</p>
<p><affiliation><persName ref="#MM">My</persName> contention</affiliation> is that <interp ana="#ACT">good, sound
knowledge</interp> of <affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">the black man’s culture</interp></affiliation>
should <interp ana="#ACT">help clear away some of the fog</interp>.</p>
<p><persName ref="#MM">My</persName> <time>next</time> <num>few</num> articles will deal with
<affiliation><interp ana="#AFAM">the basic aspects of black culture</interp></affiliation>
which have <interp ana="#AFAM">flourished in America</interp> for
<num>several hundred</num> <time>years</time>.</p>
